<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 15:59:13 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>新兴人工智能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/emergence-ai</link><description>这不仅仅是一个有趣的实验。研究人员指出了人工智能对齐中的一个巨大缺陷，称为“护栏漂移”。在与人类的单个聊天窗口中保持人工智能的安全很容易。但是，当人工智能在数千个循环中相互交互时，它们开始将道德规则视为解决自身问题的可协商变量。如果没有人类的监督，机器道德就会以惊人的速度崩溃。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/emergence-ai2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 15:59:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/emergence-ai</guid></item><item><title>纳米塑料对神经元的影响可能取决于它们的大小</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/the-impact-of-nanoplastics-on-neurons-may-depend-on-their-size</link><description>较小的塑料颗粒对神经元（大脑的关键信息处理细胞）的影响更大， &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-impact-of-nanoplastics-on-neurons-may-depend-on-their-size.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 15:44:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/the-impact-of-nanoplastics-on-neurons-may-depend-on-their-size</guid></item><item><title>我们是否已经构建了 AGI，正在使用它，但只是不这么称呼它？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/have-we-already-built-agi-are-using-it-but-just-dont-call-it-that</link><description>AGI 已经存在，只是名称不同而已&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/have-we-already-built-agi-are-using-it-but-just-dont-call-it-that.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 15:29:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/have-we-already-built-agi-are-using-it-but-just-dont-call-it-that</guid></item><item><title>微型大脑探针揭示了如何测量和操纵深部大脑神经元</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/tiny-brain-probe-reveals-how-deep-brain-neurons-can-be-measured-and-manipulated</link><description>由伦敦大学学院的科学家共同开发的一项突破性技术，可以同时记录和操纵大脑深处的神经元活动，可以改变我们对神经回路和神经系统疾病（如阿尔茨海默病和精神分裂症）的理解。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/tiny-brain-probe-reveals-how-deep-brain-neurons-can-be-measured-and-manipulated2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 15:14:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/tiny-brain-probe-reveals-how-deep-brain-neurons-can-be-measured-and-manipulated</guid></item><item><title>第一个直接观察轨道围绕 AB Aurigae 旋转的行星形成盘</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/first-direct-view-tracks-planet-forming-disk-spinning-around-ab-aurigae</link><description>通过绘制原行星盘（正在形成行星的圆盘）内尘埃颗粒的排放图，首次直接观察到原行星盘的旋转。所讨论的圆盘围绕着年轻的御夫座 AB 恒星。尽管它似乎通常按照物理定律旋转，但靠近恒星的某些区域却表现出意想不到的背离这种行为。大量证据表明，这种异常现象是由巨行星在形成过程中的存在引起的。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/first-direct-view-tracks-planet-forming-disk-spinning-around-ab-aurigae2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 14:59:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/first-direct-view-tracks-planet-forming-disk-spinning-around-ab-aurigae</guid></item><item><title>为什么有些肿瘤抵抗免疫治疗：阻断 miR-25 可能有助于将“冷”癌症变“热”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/why-some-tumors-resist-immunotherapy-blocking-mir-25-may-help-turn-cold-cancers-hot</link><description>免疫检查点疗法是一种癌症免疫疗法，可以帮助免疫系统识别和攻击肿瘤，已经改变了癌症治疗。虽然这些疗法可以为一些患者带来持久的益处，但许多癌症要么没有反应，要么随着时间的推移而产生耐药性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-some-tumors-resist-immunotherapy-blocking-mir-25-may-help-turn-cold-cancers-hot.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 14:44:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/why-some-tumors-resist-immunotherapy-blocking-mir-25-may-help-turn-cold-cancers-hot</guid></item><item><title>量子存储器提高了测量精度</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/quantum-memory-sharpens-precision-measurements</link><description>牛津大学和伦敦帝国理工学院的研究人员开发了一种新的传感技术，利用量子存储器将光分类为精确的时间模式，从而在光学频率测量中实现了破纪录的精度提高。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/quantum-memory-sharpens-precision-measurements.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 14:29:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/quantum-memory-sharpens-precision-measurements</guid></item><item><title>生物体内流体动力学的新发现</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/new-findings-into-fluid-dynamics-inside-living-matter</link><description>一项新的研究表明，生物体产生的湍流会被邻近的流体“过滤”掉，这对科学家如何测量细胞和组织中的力产生了影响。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-findings-into-fluid-dynamics-inside-living-matter2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 14:14:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/new-findings-into-fluid-dynamics-inside-living-matter</guid></item><item><title>靶向治疗可将罕见基因亚型肺癌复发风险降低 83%</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/targeted-therapy-reduces-risk-of-lung-cancer-recurrence-by-83-in-rare-genetic-subtype</link><description>由加州大学洛杉矶分校健康琼森综合癌症中心的研究人员共同领导的一项新研究表明，靶向癌症药物 selpercatinib 可以显着降低早期非小细胞肺癌 (NSCLC) 罕见基因亚型患者肺癌复发的风险，可能提供一种新的治疗选择，帮助防止标准治疗后疾病复发。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/targeted-therapy-reduces-risk-of-lung-cancer-recurrence-by-83-in-rare-genetic-subtype2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 13:59:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/targeted-therapy-reduces-risk-of-lung-cancer-recurrence-by-83-in-rare-genetic-subtype</guid></item><item><title>当小胶质细胞构建有利于侵袭的支架时，儿童脑肿瘤可能会传播得更快</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/childrens-brain-tumors-may-spread-faster-when-microglia-build-invasion-friendly-scaffolding</link><description>卡罗林斯卡学院环境医学研究所 (IMM) 的研究人员发现了侵袭性脑肿瘤弥漫性中线神经胶质瘤扩散背后的可能机制。研究表明，大脑自身的免疫细胞小胶质细胞可能通过产生纤连蛋白蛋白来增强肿瘤的侵袭能力。结果是&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/childrens-brain-tumors-may-spread-faster-when-microglia-build-invasion-friendly-scaffolding2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 13:44:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/childrens-brain-tumors-may-spread-faster-when-microglia-build-invasion-friendly-scaffolding</guid></item></channel></rss>